Terraform is declarative and not transactional ‚Äî meaning it doesn't provide a built-in ‚Äúundo‚Äù or rollback mechanism. If a terraform apply 
breaks things, you must roll back by reapplying a previous known-good state, versioned code, or using backups of the Terraform state.

